CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 31, 1954, pg. 20 reads: "Plan Frog Derby Day - chairman Roland Sawyer and his committee map final plans for Frog Derby Day, scheduled to be held Wednesday, Aug. 4, at Wheeling Downs, Wheeling, W.Va. Seated, left to right: Harold Jones, Robert M. Ratcliffe and Roland M. Sawyer.  Standing: Co-Chairman Clarence Waters and Byron Peters. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of FROGS Derby Day committee, from left, seated: Harold Jones, Robert M. Ratcliffe, and Roland M. Sawyer; standing: Clarence Waters and Byron Peters, posed in domestic interior with boat painting on wall
